    • nextPage

      public int nextPage()
      The function increments the current page being read and updates the number of pages read and last page read if necessary, and resets the current page being read if it exceeds the total number of pages. This methods is used for the readin session.
      Specified by:
      nextPage in interface INavigable
      Returns:
      The method `nextPage()` returns an integer value, which is the current page being read after the method updates the `currentPageBeingRead`, `NumberLastPageRead`, and `numberOfPagesRead` variables.

    • previousPage

      public int previousPage()
      This function decreases the current page being read by one and returns the new value, ensuring that the value does not go below zero. It is used for the readin session.
      Specified by:
      previousPage in interface INavigable
      Returns:
      The method `previousPage()` returns an integer value which represents the current page being read after decrementing it by 1.
